net.sourceforge.waters.model.module

Interface EventAliasProxy

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AliasProxy, Comparable<NamedProxy>, ComparableProxy<NamedProxy>, IdentifiedProxy, NamedProxy, Proxy
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EventAliasElement

    public interface EventAliasProxy
extends AliasProxy

    An alias representing a group of events.

    An event alias is used to give a name of a group events used together in different edges or graphs of a module. This kind of alias can occur in the event alias list of a module, or in the body of a foreach alias construct (ForeachProxy). The name of an event can be an arbitrary identifier; it can be indexed to support the use of the foreach alias construct. Its value must be an event list expression (EventListExpressionProxy).

    This interface does not contain any new methods, because all required attributes are contained in the superinterface AliasProxy. It is merely a marker interface.

    Author:
    Robi Malik
